## Summary

The first `libheif-v1.23.1` release was built from vcpkg tag
`2026.05.25`, so the zip contains **libheif 1.21.2** while the tag/asset
name claimed 1.23.1.

This PR fixes the release pipeline so republishing produces a real
1.23.1 asset.

## Changes

- Pin `vcpkg.ref` to commit `33e5269bbfc24fb252bc48a3e624c8193afdccce`
(first port with libheif **1.23.1**)
- Package script verifies `heif_version.h` / vcpkg status against
`versions.json` and fails on mismatch
- Omit `debug/` from release zips (`include_debug: false`); emit
`*.zip.sha256` sidecars
- Cache key uses `features_key` (no commas) so `actions/cache` accepts
it
- Release notes heredoc fixed (closing `"@` at column 0; expand
`$TRIPLET` correctly)
- Add scheduled **Sync libheif upstream** workflow (opens PRs when
strukturag/libheif + microsoft/vcpkg move ahead)

## After merge

1. Merge this PR (push to `main` triggers **Build libheif (Windows
MSVC)**)
2. Confirm release `libheif-v1.23.1` asset + `.sha256` report port
**1.23.1**
3. Easelâ€™s `sync-easel-deps.yml` will open a pin PR once the sidecar
exists (or run it via `workflow_dispatch`)

Companion Easel PR: https://github.com/fritz-fritz/Easel/pull/23
