Subject: [PATCH 2/5] fix(ci): avoid YAML-breaking PowerShell here-string in
 release notes (#5)

<!-- CURSOR_AGENT_PR_BODY_BEGIN -->
## Summary

The merge of #4 never ran the Windows build: the workflow YAML failed to
parse in **0s**.

PowerShell `@"..."@` here-strings put content (and the closing `"@`) at
column 0, which ends the `run: |` block scalar. Lines like `- Features:`
were then parsed as YAML and the workflow aborted before any job
started.

## Fix

Build release notes with an indented `@(...) -join "\`n"` array instead
of a here-string, so the entire script stays inside the YAML block
scalar.

## After merge

Push to `main` should trigger **Build libheif (Windows MSVC)** and
republish `libheif-v1.23.1` with a real 1.23.1 port + `.sha256` sidecar.
