<!-- CURSOR_AGENT_PR_BODY_BEGIN -->
## Summary

The corrected `libheif-v1.23.1` zip omitted `debug/` but still shipped
`AOMTargets-debug.cmake`, which references `debug/lib/aom.lib`.

`find_package(AOM)` then fails its existence check, so `AOM::aom` never
resolves. `libheif-sys` links `heif`/`libde265`/`x265` but not `aom`,
while `heif.lib` still needs aom symbols â†’ Core Windows `LNK2019`
(desktop stayed green via a stale rust-cache that still linked aom).

## Fix

When `include_debug: false`, also delete Debug CMake import fragments
(`*Targets-debug.cmake`, `*-config-debug.cmake`, etc.) from the staged
`share/` tree.

## After merge

Rebuild + republish `libheif-v1.23.1` (may need to delete the immutable
release assets first if clobber is blocked), then refresh Easelâ€™s lock
SHA256 and bump the rust-cache prefix.
