MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

gh release create prints the release URL to stdout. Assigning
`$code = Publish-Release` captured that URL plus exit 0; PowerShell's
`if ($code -eq 0)` then filtered to 0 (falsy), so the fallback loop
kept creating libheif-v1.23.1-r3â€¦r20 until it gave up.

- Discard gh stdout; throw on non-zero exit
- Create at most one rebuild tag via Get-NextRebuildTag
- Skip publish on main when a release for this version already exists
- workflow_dispatch/schedule still force a single new -rN

